uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab1_1.utils.parser

Class MZTabDataLineParser<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab1_1.utils.parser.MZTabLineParser
      • uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab1_1.utils.parser.MZTabDataLineParser<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of domain object the parser creates.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SMELineParser, SMFLineParser, SMLLineParser

    public abstract class MZTabDataLineParser<T>
extends MZTabLineParser
    This class allows the validation and loading of the data into the uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab1_1.model.MZTabRecord. NOTICE: MZTabColumnFactory maintain a couple of IMZTabColumn which have internal logical position and order. In physical mzTab file, we allow user not obey this logical position organized way, and provide their date with own order. In order to distinguish them, we use physical position (a positive integer) to record the column location in mzTab file. And use PositionMapping structure to maintain the mapping between them.
    Since:
    14/02/13
    Author:
    qingwei
    See Also:
    SMLLineParser, SMFLineParser, SMELineParser

      • MZTabDataLineParser

                              MZTabColumnFactory factory,
                              PositionMapping positionMapping,

                              MZTabErrorList errorList)
        Generate a mzTab data line parser. NOTICE: MZTabColumnFactory maintain a couple of IMZTabColumn which have internal logical position and order. In physical mzTab file, we allow user not obey this logical position organized way, and provide their date with own order. In order to distinguish them, we use physical position (a positive integer) to record the column location in mzTab file. And use PositionMapping structure the maintain the mapping between them.
        Parameters:
        context - the parser context, keeping dynamic state and lookup associations.
        factory - SHOULD NOT set null
        positionMapping - SHOULD NOT set null
        metadata - SHOULD NOT set null
        errorList - a MZTabErrorList object.

      • checkGOTerms

        protected List<String> checkGOTerms(IMZTabColumn column,
                                    String go_terms)
        Check and translate target string into string list which split by ',' character.. If parse incorrect, raise FormatErrorType.StringList error. Besides, each item in list should be start with "GO:", otherwise system raise FormatErrorType.GOTermList error. Normally, go_terms can set "null", but in "Complete" file, in general "null" values SHOULD not be given.
        Parameters:
        column - SHOULD NOT set null
        go_terms - SHOULD NOT be empty.
        Returns:
        a List object.

      • checkProteinCoverage

        protected Double checkProteinCoverage(IMZTabColumn column,
                                      String protein_coverage)
        Check and translate protein_coverage string into Double. If parse incorrect, raise FormatErrorType.Double error. protein_coverage range should be in the [0, 1), otherwise raise LogicalErrorType.ProteinCoverage error. NOTICE: If ratios are included and the denominator is zero, the "INF" value MUST be used. If the result leads to calculation errors (for example 0/0), this MUST be reported as "not a number" ("NaN").
        Parameters:
        column - SHOULD NOT set null
        protein_coverage - SHOULD NOT be empty.
        Returns:
        a Double object.

        protected String checkSequence(IMZTabColumn column,
                               String sequence)

        Parameters:
        column - SHOULD NOT set null
        sequence - SHOULD NOT be empty.
        Returns:
        a String object.

      • checkCalcMassToCharge

        protected Double checkCalcMassToCharge(IMZTabColumn column,
                                       String calc_mass_to_charge)
        Check and translate calc_mass_to_charge string into Double. If parse incorrect, raise FormatErrorType.Double error. NOTICE: If ratios are included and the denominator is zero, the "INF" value MUST be used. If the result leads to calculation errors (for example 0/0), this MUST be reported as "not a number" ("NaN").
        Parameters:
        column - SHOULD NOT set null
        calc_mass_to_charge - SHOULD NOT be empty.
        Returns:
        a Double object.
